Package org.spongepowered.api.effect.particle

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    ParticleEffect
    Represents a particle effect that can be send to the Minecraft client.
    ParticleEffect.Colorable
    Represents a colored particle effect.
    ParticleEffect.Material
    Represents a particle effect that needs a item stack to be rendered on the client.
    ParticleEffect.Note
    Represents a particle effect that uses a note value.
    ParticleEffect.Resizable
    Represents a resized particle effect.
    ParticleEffectBuilder
    Represents a builder to create a ParticleEffect.
    ParticleEffectBuilder.Colorable
    Represents a particle builder to create a ParticleEffect.Colorable.
    ParticleEffectBuilder.Material
    Represents a particle builder to create a ParticleEffect.Material.
    ParticleEffectBuilder.Note
    Represents a particle builder to create a ParticleEffect.Note.
    ParticleEffectBuilder.Resizable
    Represents a particle builder to create a ParticleEffect.Resizable.
    ParticleType
    Represents a particle that can be sent on a Minecraft client.
    ParticleType.Colorable
    Represents a particle that can be colored.
    ParticleType.Material
    Represents a particle that utilizes a item stack to be able to render on the client.
    ParticleType.Note
    Represents a particle that uses a note value.
    ParticleType.Resizable
    Represents a particle that can be resized.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ParticleTypes
    The particles that can be sent on a vanilla Minecraft client.
